714179f-a.text:
124-128 East 65th Street, south side, between Park and
Lexington Avenues.
bout 1911.
Gift of E. M. Jenks.
I think it is 120-124 East 65th Street, south side, between Park and Lexington Avenues.  As per the date, I would have thought 1933-35, but that is only a guess.

714180f-a.text:
116-120 East 65th Street, south side, between Park and

722308f-a.text:
620 Park Avenue, at N. W. corner of 65th Street, a new apertment
building nearing completion.
It replaces the old 7-story Palacio apartments.
Early 1924.
Cift of E.M. Jenks.
NNG ~3788

722310f-a.text:
Park Avenue, east side, south from E. 87th to 65th Streets, and showing prominently the Seventh Regiment Armory occunying the 67th -66th Street frontage. This structure, built in 1878-80 formerly had a pointed steeple where the flag is flying.. The photographer is viewing same from a similar vantage point in both instances (S.W. corner of Park Avenue and 88th Street) and shows the changed railing used in fencfnm the center plot dividing the
traffic lanes.
June 8, 1028.
V1ee 2: April 25, 1238.
P.L. Sperr
